Hmmm....my script now looks like this:

   #!/bin/zsh
   setopt extendedglob

   if [ ! -d ./EXIF ]
   then
       mkdir ./EXIF ]
   fi    
   
   for i in **/*.jpg                    <<<<<---- line 9
   do
       echo -n "examine $i..."
       idx=0;
       fn=$(basename $i .jpg)
       fnex=${fn}.exif-${idx}.txt
       while [ -f ./EXIF/${fnex} ]
       do
           idx=$(( idx + 1 ))
           fnex=${fn}.exif-${idx}.txt
       done
       print "...writing ./EXIF/${fnex}"
       jhead -v $i > ./EXIF/${fnex}
   done

...but...still getting this:

./mkexif.sh:9: no matches found: **/*.jpg

After all this I must confess: My confusion became now one of my 
lesser problems... ;O)

